Question: PAP of the sunset today? Or PAP of the sunset from a previous day!
Answer: I had a realization recently about happiness and pain. I think I used to think that the two can’t exist at the same time. I spent a lot of my life repressing my feelings and ignoring my pain. I wanted people to think I was put together and I was okay and that there was nothing wrong with me. A couple years ago I had a bit of an awakening to my own pain and I felt like I wanted to shout it from the rooftops. I wanted everyone to know I am in pain! I don’t have everything together! I’m not perfect! People have wronged me very deeply! I wanted to make my pain real. I wanted it to matter. And I think in the process of doing that, I started to over-identify with it. I started to think “I AM my pain” rather than “I am IN pain”. I think that was necessary at the time because of my natural inclination to dismiss myself. But recently I decided I don’t want to hold onto pain so tightly. I used to think that “cheering yourself up” was a hoax because if you have a problem, it’s a problem and cheering yourself up is not gonna change it. That is true, but I’m learning that life is not so black and white. You can be going through extreme pain and still have moments of happiness. In the midst of a tragedy you can feel gratitude for the good in the world. In an extremely stressful time you can decide to do something fun and have fun and be carefree for a moment. None of those things will change what happened. None of those things will fix your problems or the problems of the world, but they can bring a little bit of light to the darkness. Turning on a lamp when it’s dark doesn’t change the fact that it’s nighttime. Turning on a flashlight doesn’t mean you’re ignoring the dark. It just makes it easier to continue on through the night. You need some light in the dark to be able to keep going. It’s okay to turn a light on. And we can’t forget that it can never be so dark that light cannot pierce through. Even in the dead of night the stars and the moon still shine. 💫

Question:
Miss Lauren
Now, what's the story behind this name ''Rabbit Hole''?
Answer: This song is about plotting your own demise. It’s about going after someone who you KNOW is never gonna be with you. It’s not gonna work, it’s not gonna happen, you’re just gonna end up with a broken heart. BUT you are desperately lonely and you also have some mental issues so you do it anyway. smh. I wanted to capture the roller coaster of emotion that comes with choosing such a dark fate for yourself so this is one of the weirdest songs I’ve ever written. It changes keys like 10 times and each section kinda sounds like a different song. But when you put it all together it’s a perfect disaster. An illusory journey of sorts. Much like when Alice fell down the rabbit hole and found Wonderland. Kinda fun, kinda scary. A nice escape from reality, but ultimately a delusional dream from beginning to end. And when you wake up from it, you are just as alone as you were before it all started.

RABBIT HOLE OUT NEXT FRIDAY 7/3 🐇 This song is about plotting your own demise. It’s about going after someone who you KNOW is never gonna be with you. It’s not gonna work, it’s not gonna happen, you’re just gonna end up with a broken heart. BUT you are desperately lonely and you also have some mental issues so you do it anyway. smh. I wanted to capture the roller coaster of emotion that comes with choosing such a dark fate for yourself so this is one of the weirdest songs I’ve ever written. It changes keys like 10 times and each section kinda sounds like a different song. But when you put it all together it’s a perfect disaster. An illusory journey of sorts. Much like when Alice fell down the rabbit hole and found Wonderland. Kinda fun, kinda scary. A nice escape from reality, but ultimately a delusional dream from beginning to end. And when you wake up from it, you are just as alone as you were before it all started.

I looked out the window and around in the floor to see if there was maybe a little rodent running around but there was nothing running around inside or anything outside that would've made it just fall. Then we went to a haunted prison for like a family reunion day before we went and grabbed lunch together. We were down in the lower level that's like the basement area I think it was called the isolation cells or something  and I begin to feel really nauseated  and feeling like overheated and choked off.. so I sat down on an old bench and I just took my phone out and opened the camera app and turned off the flash and just aimed it to look behind me weirdly I didnt notice anything when I was uploading the pictures from that day but on the one specific  photo my friend posted out a glare and what appeared to be a face in the area I sat down in.
